    },
    {
      "name": "--- PHASE 2: Kafka Simulation (G7 & G9) ---",
      "description": "Simulates Kafka messages from G7 (vehicles) and G9 (incidents) directly into the listeners.\n\nThese endpoints are only active when SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE != prod.\nThey bypass the Kafka broker entirely and call the listener methods directly — functionally identical to receiving a real message.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "20 - Vehicle Event from G7 (CLOTURE)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/test/kafka/vehicule",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "test",
                "kafka",
                "vehicule"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"vehicleId\": \"BUS_404\",\n  \"line\": \"L1\",\n  \"status\": \"ACTIVE\",\n  \"speed\": 45.2,\n  \"delayMinutes\": 2,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-07T10:00:00\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "Simulates a Kafka message from G7 on topic g8.vehicule.status.\n\nExpected: 200 OK — \"Vehicle Kafka event simulated successfully\"\nExpected MongoDB: new IncomingEvent with sourceType=VEHICLE containing vehicleId, line, status, speed, delayMinutes."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "21 - Incident CLOTURE from G9 (Should be saved)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/test/kafka/incident",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "test",
                "kafka",
                "incident"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"reference\": \"INC-2026-TEST\",\n  \"source\": \"IOT\",\n  \"type\": \"PANNE_VEHICULE\",\n  \"gravite\": \"CRITIQUE\",\n  \"statut\": \"CLOTURE\",\n  \"vehiculeId\": \"BUS_404\",\n  \"ligneTransport\": \"Ligne 15\",\n  \"declarantId\": 0,\n  \"responsableId\": 42,\n  \"description\": \"Surchauffe du moteur d\\u00e9tect\\u00e9e par le capteur thermique.\",\n  \"latitude\": 33.57311,\n  \"longitude\": -7.589843,\n  \"dateSignalement\": \"2026-05-06T14:30:00\",\n  \"dateIncident\": \"2026-05-06T14:28:00\",\n  \"dateResolution\": \"2026-05-06T16:45:00\",\n  \"dateLimiteResolution\": \"2026-05-06T16:30:00\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "Simulates a resolved incident from G9 on topic incident.analytique.topic.\n\nTransformations applied by IncidentKafkaListener:\n- gravite CRITIQUE → severity CRITICAL\n- zone = \"33.573,-7.590\" (rounded to 3dp, ~110m grid)\n- resolutionMinutes = Duration(14:28 → 16:45) = 137 min\n\nExpected: 200 OK — \"Incident Kafka event simulated successfully\"\nExpected MongoDB: new IncomingEvent with sourceType=INCIDENT, severity=CRITICAL, resolutionMinutes=137, zone=\"33.573,-7.590\""
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "22 - Incident EN_COURS from G9 (Should be IGNORED)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/test/kafka/incident",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "test",
                "kafka",
                "incident"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"reference\": \"INC-2026-IGNORED\",\n  \"source\": \"IOT\",\n  \"type\": \"PANNE_VEHICULE\",\n  \"gravite\": \"CRITIQUE\",\n  \"statut\": \"EN_COURS\",\n  \"vehiculeId\": \"BUS_404\",\n  \"ligneTransport\": \"Ligne 15\",\n  \"declarantId\": 0,\n  \"responsableId\": 42,\n  \"description\": \"This should be ignored \\u2014 not a final status\",\n  \"latitude\": 33.57311,\n  \"longitude\": -7.589843,\n  \"dateSignalement\": \"2026-05-06T14:30:00\",\n  \"dateIncident\": \"2026-05-06T14:28:00\",\n  \"dateResolution\": \"2026-05-06T16:45:00\",\n  \"dateLimiteResolution\": \"2026-05-06T16:30:00\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "Tests the statut filter: only CLOTURE and ANNULE are accepted.\n\nExpected: 200 OK (listener handles it gracefully without crashing)\nExpected MongoDB: NO new document saved for this reference\nCheck logs for: \"Incident event ignored because status is not final: statut=EN_COURS\""
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "23 - Malformed JSON Vehicle Event (Error Resilience)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/test/kafka/vehicule",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "test",
                "kafka",
                "vehicule"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "this is not valid json {{{",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "text"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "Tests error resilience: the listener must catch JsonProcessingException and NOT crash.\n\nA bad Kafka message must never kill the consumer thread.\n\nExpected: 500 Internal Server Error (the controller catches and surfaces the error)\nExpected: Service continues running normally — all subsequent calls still work\nCheck logs for: JsonProcessingException"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "--- WAIT ~60 SECONDS FOR SCHEDULER ---",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "07 - Health Check (Ping)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/dashboard",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "analytics",
                "dashboard"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Send this immediately after ingesting to confirm the service is alive. The values will still be zero until the scheduler runs (every 60 seconds). After ~60 seconds, re-send this request and the values should reflect your ingested data."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
